I set up postback with RedTrack, and it  tracking clicks but does not show cost is there another way to update it

It sounds like there might be an issue with the setup of your postback. Let's go through the steps to ensure everything is set up correctly. First, can you confirm that you've followed all the steps in our guide for setting up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak? You can find the detailed instructions here: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). If everything is set up correctly and you're still facing issues, you might want to check if the cost parameter is being passed correctly in your postback URL. Let me know if you need further assistance!
Should i add cost parameter manually in postback url

Yes, you should ensure that the cost parameter is included in your postback URL. You can manually add it if it's not already there. Make sure to follow the correct format for including parameters in the URL. If you need detailed guidance on how to do this, please refer to our article on setting up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). If you have any specific questions or run into issues, feel free to ask!
should i use cost={cost} this parameter for cost update in postback

Yes, you should use the parameter `cost={cost}` in your postback URL to update the cost. This will ensure that the cost data is correctly passed back to NewsBreak. Make sure that `{cost}` is dynamically replaced with the actual cost value from your tracking system. If you need more detailed instructions, please refer to our guide: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). Let me know if you need any further assistance!
When event value show true when a conversion happen

The event value will show as true when a conversion happens if you have set up your postback URL correctly and included the necessary parameters. Make sure that your postback URL includes the `event_type` and `nb_value` parameters, which are essential for tracking conversions and their values. For example, your postback URL should look something like this: `http://business.newsbreak.com/tracking/attribute?callback=your_callback_id&event_type=complete_payment&nb_value=50`. If everything is set up correctly, you should see the event value as true when a conversion occurs. For more detailed instructions, please refer to our guide: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). Let me know if you need any further assistance!
so in this postback url i add cost parameter

Yes, you should add the cost parameter to your postback URL to ensure that the cost data is tracked correctly. Your postback URL should include the `cost` parameter along with other necessary parameters like `callback`, `event_type`, and `nb_value`. For example, your postback URL might look something like this: `http://business.newsbreak.com/tracking/attribute?callback=your_callback_id&event_type=complete_payment&nb_value=50&cost={cost}`. Make sure that `{cost}` is dynamically replaced with the actual cost value from your tracking system. For more detailed instructions, please refer to our guide: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). Let me know if you need any further assistance!
cost is not showing yrt i redtrack

If the cost is not showing in RedTrack, there might be an issue with how the cost parameter is being passed in your postback URL. Here are a few steps to troubleshoot this issue: 
1. **Check the Postback URL**: Ensure that the `cost` parameter is correctly included in your postback URL. It should look something like this: `http://business.newsbreak.com/tracking/attribute?callback=your_callback_id&event_type=complete_payment&nb_value=50&cost={cost}`.
2. **Dynamic Token Replacement**: Make sure that `{cost}` is dynamically replaced with the actual cost value from your tracking system.
3. **RedTrack Configuration**: Verify that RedTrack is configured to pass and receive the cost parameter correctly. You may need to check RedTrack's documentation or support for specific instructions on how to set this up.
4. **Testing**: Test your postback URL to ensure that it is working correctly and passing all necessary parameters, including cost.
For more detailed instructions, please refer to our guide: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). If you continue to experience issues, you might want to reach out to RedTrack support for further assistance.

So can i add api access token to redtrack

For detailed instructions on how to integrate the API, you can refer to this guide: [API Integration Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/27680147056397-API-Integration-Guide). So if i add api access token the cost will be show in redtrack like the ou r problem can be solved with this mehod
